<span class="header1">PUBLIC SERVICE</span>
<p>The occupations in this field need people who are active and enthusiastic and who do not mind hard work.</p>

<hr size="1" />

	<span class="header2">Public Health Care Investigator</span><br /><br />
	<span class="header3">Job Description</span>
	<blockquote>If you like to find solutions to problems and solve mysteries, you might become a public health care investigator.  In this job, you would find, prevent, and control diseases.  You would interview patients and gather statistics.  You would report what you found to local and state health departments and physicians.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Education</span>
	<blockquote>You need at least a Bachelor's Degree for this job.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Salary</span>
	<blockquote>The yearly salary ranged from $15,000 to $36,000.</blockquote>

<hr size="1" />

	<span class="header2">Police Officer</span><br /><br />
	<img class="job_pic" src="/images/icons/GH/43135.jpg" width="100" height="100" border="0" alt="Police Officer" />
	<span class="header3">Job Description</span>
	<blockquote>If you want to help keep your community safe, you might become a police officer.  In this job, you would patrol the community to make sure that those who live and work there are safe.  You would investigate crimes, settle arguments, and even write tickets.  You would need to have good writing skills so that you could write reports on the cases you handle.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Education</span>
	<blockquote>It is better to have a Bachelor's Degree in this occupation.  However, some communities will hire police officers who do not have a degree.  All officers must attend a police academy where they learn police procedure and regulations.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Salary</span>
	<blockquote>The yearly salary ranges from $24,000 to $50,000 and depends on the community's ability to pay.</blockquote>

<hr size="1" />

	<span class="header2">Security Guard</span><br /><br />
	<img class="job_pic" src="/images/icons/GH/43109.jpg" width="100" height="100" border="0" alt="Security Guard" />
	<span class="header3">Job Description</span>
	<blockquote>As a security guard, you would patrol a building to make property was not stolen, and that no one was trespassing.  Many security guards work at night. Others work during the day while workers are in the building.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Education</span>
	<blockquote>You need a high school diploma for this job.  You also need a valid driver's license.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Salary</span>
	<blockquote>Security guards are paid by the hour. The hourly wage ranges from $6.00 to $12.00.</blockquote>

<hr size="1" />

<span class="header1">SOCIAL/MENTAL</span>
<p>The occupations in this field deal with public health.  Those who work in these occupations work to prevent disease and to encourage community well-being.</p>

<hr size="1" />

	<span class="header2">Dentist</span><br /><br />
	<img class="job_pic" src="/images/icons/GH/C506031.jpg" width="100" height="100" border="0" alt="Dentist" />
	<span class="header3">Job Description</span>
	<blockquote>A dentist helps people keep their teeth healthy and clean.  A dentist who works for the public health department not only works with individual patients, he/she also works with community health dental programs.  If you were a dentist for the health department, you might talk to students or to community groups about dental care.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Education</span>
	<blockquote>You need to have a Bachelor's Degree.  You also need to complete a doctorate degree from a dental school to be a dentist. You must also be licensed by the state.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Salary</span>
	<blockquote>The yearly salary ranges from $39,000 to $70,000+.</blockquote>

<hr size="1" />

	<span class="header2">Physician</span><br /><br />
	<img class="job_pic" src="/images/icons/GH/1152.jpg" width="100" height="100" border="0" alt="Physician" />
	<span class="header3">Job Description</span>
	<blockquote>A physician is a medical doctor.  If you were a doctor for the health department, you would promote wellness through community programs.  You would be responsible for making sure the programs were available to those who needed it.  For example, vaccinations are required for children.  You would make sure that announcements were made so that parents would bring their children to be vaccinated.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Education</span>
	<blockquote>You need a Bachelor's Degree.  In addition, you must graduate from medical school.  An internship and residency in a hospital are also required.  You must be licensed by the state.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Salary</span>
	<blockquote>The yearly salary ranges from $120,000 to $200,000.</blockquote>

<hr size="1" />

	<span class="header2">Public Health Social Worker</span><br /><br />
	<img class="job_pic" src="/images/icons/GH/1212.jpg" width="100" height="100" border="0" alt="Public Health Social Worker">
	<span class="header3">Job Description</span>
	<blockquote>Social work is about helping. As a public health social worker, you would interview a family and others who know them.  You would be looking for information that would allow you to improve the family's health and well-being.  You would complete paperwork documenting what you found and did.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Education</span>
	<blockquote>You need a Bachelor's Degree to become a social worker at an entry-level. Those with more responsible positions must have a master's degree.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Salary</span>
	<blockquote>The yearly salary ranges from $15,000 to $44,000.</blockquote>

