<span class="header1">ENVIRONMENT</span>
<p>The occupations in this field need those who are willing to research and explore nature.</p>

<hr size="1" />

	<span class="header2">Environmental Lawyer</span><br /><br />
	<img class="job_pic" src="/images/icons/GH/1360.jpg" width="100" height="100" border="0" alt="Environmental Lawyer" />
	<span class="header3">Job Description</span>
	<blockquote>If you want to influence how people and organizations use the earth's environment, this occupation may be for you.  To practice environmental law, you must understand the law and communicate well.  You must also be organized and able to negotiate with others.  If you become an environmental lawyer, you might develop a legal case or appear in court to prevent the building of a road through a wilderness area.  Or, you might defend a logging company's right to build that road.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Education</span>
	<blockquote>You will need a Bachelor's Degree and three years of law school to be an environmental lawyer. You must also pass the state "bar exam." To learn about nature sciences and city and rural development, volunteer with political action groups concerned about the environment.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Salary</span>
	<blockquote>Environmental lawyer salaries range from $35,000 to $80,000.</blockquote>

<hr size="1" />

	<span class="header2">Ecologist</span><br /><br />
	<span class="header3">Job Description</span>
	<blockquote>An ecologist is a scientist who studies the effect that people and animals have on the earth's environment.  If you are concerned about harm to the environment and have good computer skills, this may be a good job for you.  As an environmentalist, you would conduct field studies.  You would also work in laboratories. Computer skills are very important in this job.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Education</span>
	<blockquote>You need a Bachelor's Degree to become an ecologist.  Most employers look for a Master's Degree and experience.  To get experience, volunteer with groups who work to protect the environment.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Salary</span>
	<blockquote>The yearly salary ranges from $22,000 to $28,000. Those with a master's degree and experience can earn $60,000.</blockquote>

<hr size="1" />

	<span class="header2">Meteorologist Technician</span><br /><br />
	<img class="job_pic" src="/images/icons/GH/1285.jpg" width="100" height="100" border="0" alt="Environmental Lawyer" />
	<span class="header3">Job Description</span>
	<blockquote>Meteorology is the science that studies the weather.  You may be very interested in the weather, but you may not want to become a meteorologist.  If so, you might become a meteorologist technician. In this job, you would work with a meteorologist to study and predict the weather.  You would use special tools and instruments to gather the information needed.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Education</span>
	<blockquote>You need a Bachelor's Degree or military training for this job.  Many employers  prefer those with military training.  They bring practical experience to the job.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Salary</span>
	<blockquote>The yearly salary ranges from $20,000 to $25,000.</blockquote>

<hr size="1" />

<span class="header1">SCIENCE/MEDICAL</span>
<p>There are many occupations that combine medicine and science.</p>

<hr size="1" />

	<span class="header2">Nurse</span><br /><br />
	<img class="job_pic" src="/images/icons/GH/1329.jpg" width="100" height="100" border="0" alt="Nurse" />
	<span class="header3">Job Description</span>
	<blockquote>As a nurse, you might help a doctor care for his or her patients.  You might care for patients in a hospital.  You would give shots, record a patient's progress, and assist the doctor in any medical procedures.  You must enjoy working with people to be good at this occupation.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Education</span>
	<blockquote>There are different levels of nursing and each has its own educational requirements.  Nursing school is required for all.  In addition, a licensing exam must be passed.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Salary</span>
	<blockquote>The yearly salary ranges from $20,000 to $60,000.</blockquote>

<hr size="1" />

	<span class="header2">Dietitian</span><br /><br />
	<img class="job_pic" src="/images/icons/GH/C577054.jpg" width="100" height="100" border="0" alt="Dietitian" />
	<span class="header3">Job Description</span>
	<blockquote>As a dietitian, you would make suggestions for good nutrition at hospitals, schools, and other institutions.  You might create menus.  You might make sure that food is prepared in a healthy way.  You might even go into a patient's home to plan appropriate meals. You would also try to educate people on how to eat properly.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Education</span>
	<blockquote>You need a Bachelor's Degree in nutrition or a health related subject for this job.  You must also complete an internship under an experienced dietitian.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Salary</span>
	<blockquote>The yearly salary ranges from $20,000 to $36,000.</blockquote>

<hr size="1" />

	<span class="header2">Paramedic</span><br /><br />
	<span class="header3">Job Description</span>
	<blockquote>In many emergencies, an ambulance is called.  A person who works in an ambulance is called a paramedic.  As a paramedic, you would be a part of a team that helps injured or sick people in emergency situations. You would provide first aid or emergency care.  You might also take the patient to the hospital.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Education</span>
	<blockquote>You need a high school diploma.  You also need training as an emergency medical technician for this job.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Salary</span>
	<blockquote>The yearly salary ranges from $28,000 to $40,000.</blockquote>

